{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4045ff27-5ab2-4303-abde-9fd6efdde36e","content":"\n\nHere are the most common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (`dotnet new`)**\n- `webapi` — minimal API template\n- `webapi --auth Individual` — JWT Bearer with ASP.NET Identity\n- `webapi --auth IndividualB2C` — Azure AD B2C\n- `webapi --auth SingleOrg` — Azure AD (single tenant)\n- `webapi --auth MultiOrg` — Azure AD (multi-tenant)\n- `webapi --auth Windows` — Windows/Negotiate auth\n\n**Node.js / Express**\n- Use `express-generator` + add `passport` (strategies: JWT, OAuth2, Local)\n- Or `fastify` with `@fastify/jwt` / `@fastify/oauth2`\n\n**Python / FastAPI**\n- `fastapi` with `python-jose` (JWT), `authlib` (OAuth2), or `fastapi-users`\n\n**Java / Spring Boot**\n- `spring-boot-starter-web` + `spring-boot-starter-security`\n- Options: JWT, OAuth2 Resource Server, LDAP, SAML\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a project with a specific stack and auth method?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"88e37007-ee5a-4cc6-8a46-079a05adb77d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most popular options.","outputTokens":349},"id":"e59ebbb4-aa3e-4a9f-9956-4ba1d429e6a0","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:55:41.981Z","parentId":"07d656fb-90ba-4830-bf11-1d4962b6bd24"}
